Architecture governance:

Before planning features or decomposing work, check `.project-manager/ARCHITECTURE.md` for:

- Which **domains** the work touches (Section 2: Domain Map)
- The canonical **data flow** path (Section 3)
- Where **types** belong (Section 4: Type Boundaries — `@shared` vs `client/src/types` vs `server/src/types`)
- **Domain-specific naming** and key orchestrators (Section 5)
- Established **patterns** to follow or extend (Section 6)

When creating new composables, components, types, or routes, follow the domain conventions. When work crosses domain boundaries, document the cross-domain dependency in the planning doc **Analysis** section. Heuristic alignment checks may use `.project-manager/ARCHITECTURE_DOMAINS.json`.
